body.name: The Humble Co. Bamboo Toothbrushes (5pk) – Toothbrushes for Superior Oral Care, Dental Hygiene, and Gum Care, BPA Free (Soft Bristles)

byLineInfo.name: Visit the The Humble Co. Store

features: TOOTHBRUSHES FOR A GOOD CONSCIENCE: Your purchase supports a child in need since, for every bamboo toothbrush sold, a child in need receives a toothbrush or alternative dental care product.

DENTIST RECOMMENDED AND DEVELOPED: Our toothbrushes are designed by dentists to help you eliminate bad breath while offering cavity protection, gum protection and working as an effective plaque remover. This nylon bristle toothbrush is for everyone, including those with sensitive gums.
PREMIUM BAMBOO: You can have great oral hygiene while still supporting sustainability. These plant based toothbrushes are made from bamboo and are vegan cruelty free products.

BPA-FREE BRISTLES: Find your perfect tooth brush, since our Humble Brush comes with a range of nylon bristles, for a medium, soft, or ultra soft bamboo toothbrush. Pick what is best for your gum sensitivity for healthy gums, fresh breath, and to remove plaque.

FOR HEALTHIER PEOPLE ON A HEALTHIER PLANET - SUPPORT US ON OUR MISSION - Please help us on our humble mission by continuing to purchase our products, however, if you for some reason would not be happy with your product just contact us and we will do everything in our power to make it right! Go Humble, Gives Smiles.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Did not disappoint
reviews.reviewText: I was worried about trying a bamboo toothbrush for fear that it would get dull immediately or not be as durable as my standard Oral-B or whatever. But these toothbrushes are great, I have had them for a while and still am on my first brush, and it doesn't feel dull or worn at all. I would buy these again and not miss my old plastic brushes at all.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great. Better than the first delivery
reviews.reviewText: The first shipment I received, the box was beat up but the internal product was unharmed. I don't know if this was the seller's fault or the shipping company, that being Amazon. This second shipment was perfect. Also, on the kids version of these toothbrush, I found them to be too stiff. This ones that I just got are adult ultra soft and they are much softer than the kids version. Overall, I'm happy with this second shipment.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for kids!
reviews.reviewText: I love these toothbrushes! My kids love the bright colors and I love that it's made from quality materials. I purchased these because I was looking for a nontoxic toothbrush option. I love that these are BPA free and easy to travel with for vacations.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 15, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good but needs some work
reviews.reviewText: I love the idea, very earth conscious and that’s what hooked me. The bristles are great and clean well but the handle is far too thin and small to hold comfortably. I also worry that the brush absorbs a lot of water and will go soft on me but they’re sturdy

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My son loves them
reviews.reviewText: I ordered these for my 3 almost 4 year old. I am trying to put my meager money where my mouth is in regards to my concern for the environment. I figure if I raise him to live in a conscientious manner from the start, then it will be easier for him to adapt as our world changes.He LOVES these toothbrushes.The only problem is that he’s obsessed with the rainbow one. Swapping to a single color is going to be fun lol.These fit great in his hand. They have very soft bristles, hold the toothpaste well and seem to have his excitement to brush reinvigorated.Handles are bamboo and the bristles are recyclable. These are cheaper than the plastic ones at the grocery store so I will continue to buy these in the future

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: They are cute, environmentally friendly, individually wrapped, colorful and great for guests.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars ~ Beautiful Bamboo Toothbrushes, Different Color Bristles on Each, Lovely Guest Toothbrushes. ~
reviews.reviewText: I like that these Organic, Eco-Friendly, Biodegradable Humble Company Natural Bamboo Toothbrushes come in a set of five different color bristle heads so that they can be kept in the same drawer and we can all tell which one is ours easily and quickly. Love that the handles are compostable and the bristles are recyclable, as we all go through so many toothbrushes over time. The heads of these toothbrushes are small and are easy to fit all sides of the teeth to brush well. They are soft enough to not damage our teeth and gums, but hard enough to clean very well. They're actually very beautiful. They also make a great guest toothbrush. I love that they are each individually wrapped. I did not realize that until I received them. Nice product; fair price. We're very happy with these toothbrushes!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Eco-Friendly but NOT Cruelty-Free due to sourcing from DuPont.
reviews.reviewText: I needed a new brush and am seeking one that is eco-friendly, sustainable, uses recyclables to create products, has combustible packing, animal cruelty free, labor practice friendly, has complete transparency w/their customers, that works, affordable, doesn’t sell in countries that mandates testing on animals in any way except for pharma (only b/c every country has that mandate to this date unfortunately) or conduct unfair/bad labor practices, etc.This hits many of those points but —****BECAUSE they source their nylon bristles from DuPont, they are not a 100% animal cruelty free company.For the product review.Packaging is nice. Quality of the handle is really good sturdy bamboo, I have not researched enough within this company to ensure it is being harvested in the best way or where they source their bamboo from etc.Bristles definitely need some work, their really hard nylon. I ordered a medium.Has a small bristle coverage area comparing, so expect it to take longer to brush, also may have to add a 2nd round of toothpaste, don’t know if it’s the bristle size or the nylon or what that dissipates the paste fast but I have to now do a double paste application.No go if you are like me and animal cruelty free is a top priority along with other earth/universe/people saver points.Update:Got used to the bristles. Don’t have to apply a 2nd round of paste I just don’t add water before brushing now after paste is applied to brush. Bristles are ok now I know not to push at all. In the end to not waste $, as they are compostable, I will be using a different company because they do source from DuPont and also do not hit on a few other points I seek to have covered in the area of saving the world so to speak.

reviews.reviewTitle: Muy buenos productos; satisfechos con la compra!
reviews.reviewText: Mi familia es de 5 integrantes, así k este paquete nos cayó de maravilla pues salieron en 70 pesos c/u . las cerdas son suaves y tienen forma curva. Ademas son de excelente calidad y contribuyes a muy buenas causas.

Look like good quality toothbrushes. I will have to update after a couple of months of use.The toothbrushes are individually wrapped in paper bags in the box. However the whole package was wrapped in plastic which is an unfortunate choice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: Easy to identify whose is whose
reviews.reviewText: I am especially pleased that these toothbrushes are soft enough for children, in a range of colours so they don't get muddled up. Anyone preferring a medium hard brush may find these a little too soft but they are a great spare and ideal for travelling. We always dry them with the brush head upright and never let them sit with wet around them and so far there have been no issues with the handle or bristle area discolouring. Very pleased with these, my first experience of bamboo toothbrushes.
